The paper discusses methods for automatically acquiring background knowledge for program induction, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach involves inductive logic programming (ILP), which is a subfield of logic programming (cs.PL) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the idea of forgetting, which is a concept in software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning.
